<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can&#8217;t finish the Superhuman cost without heavily mentioning AI. The newly added Ask AI feature is the absolute star. Similar to reading a Replit review for code generation, this tool generates professional text. The Auto-Summarize tool is also highly highlighted. The tool places 1-line summaries right above long, tedious threads. Additionally, it offers an Instant Reply feature that drafts context-aware responses automatically. Over time, the system actively learns your specific voice and tone to generate even better drafts.</span></p>
<h4><span style="font-weight: 400;">Read Statuses and Reminders</span></h4>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Another of the Superhuman features is that it has built-in, invisible open tracking. Consider that you don&#8217;t need clunky third-party tracking extensions anymore. Test the &#8220;Remind me if no reply&#8221; function. It literally pings the thread back to your inbox automatically if ignored. What does Superhuman do to your follow-ups? It makes them completely effortless.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Superhuman Email Review</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The table is transparent about what you get. While most feedback is generally glowing, there are distinct downsides to consider. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We found minor privacy concerns regarding how AI processes your data, though they have a zero-retention policy with OpenAI. When using the software, you are granting it full read/write access to your digital life. It is powerful, but it requires massive trust. This impacts how some security-focused teams view the platform. However, as a highly secure client, it holds strict SOC 2 compliance.</span></p>
